French state-owned Banque Nationale deParis is planning a one-for-10 capital increase in the next fewmonths, the bank announced at its annual press conference.    BNP is planning to distribute one new share or investmentcertificate for every 10 held.    The French state is a 99.97 pct shareholder in the bank,which is due for privatisation during the next five years underthe government's plan to return 65 state-owned banks, insurancecompanies and industrial groups to the private sector. REUTER&#3;